I believe this may be a duplicate of #890881.
I tried bringing the single-disk array that SRT configures with `mdadm --assemble --scan` and got an error:
mdmon: (IMSM): Unsupported attributes : 2000000 mdmon: Unsupported attributes in IMSM metadata.Arrays activation is blocked.
A more reasonable behaviour would be to block activation of the cache member, but allow the non-cache member to activate as usual.
I'm proposing a patch that at least allows device detection to continue when faced with an md member with incomplete or invalid metadata.
